alert.note: Alert for St. Louis (Minnesota) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.senderName: NWS Duluth (Northeast Minnesota and Northern Wisconsin)
info.headline: Flood Warning issued May 20 at 10:43AM CDT until further notice by NWS Duluth
info.description: ...FLOOD WARNING NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL 2 PM CDT SATURDAY... * WHAT...Flooding continues but is subsiding on the Cloquet River. * WHERE...A portion of northeast Minnesota, including the following county, St. Louis. * WHEN...Until 200 PM CDT Saturday. * IMPACTS...Flooding of rivers, creeks, streams, and other low-lying and flood-prone locations is occurring. Several structures are flooded and some sand bagging operations are continuing. Low-water crossings are inundated with water and may not be passable. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 1028 AM CDT, The Cloquet River is receding from its crest. Releases from Island Lake Reservoir have been reduced and additional reductions are expected. - Some locations that will experience flooding include... Boman Lake and Hunter Lake. Areas down stream adjacent to the Cloquet River.
info.instruction: Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles. Please report observed flooding to local emergency services or law enforcement and request they pass this information to the National Weather Service when you can do so safely.
